content.description: Crux is near the beginning. 2-3 pads is sufficient protection. Moves are good but dab factor decreases quality.
content.location: Immediately to the left of the corridor (Oval Office, fish and grits etc.). Walk between boulders and shimmy into the landing area.

content.description: Start sitting on right side of face matched on right facing sidepull.  Trend low and left, gain the arete, then top out.
content.protection: pads, landing is kinda janky at the moment.
content.location: fifteen feet right of Liger or so.

content.description: Start low on a left hand jug and a higher right crimper. Climb up the outer part of the overhang arete onto several well deserved jug rails above.
content.location: On the entrance to the cave where Iron Jesus is.

content.description: Start on two good edges and work you way up jugs to fun top-out.
content.location: On boulder before you walk in to the corridor with Liger.

content.description: Start crouched in the pit, with your right hand on a triangle pinch, and left on a low incut sidepull. Climb up and left. Move left around the arete on pretty good holds to top out high above a jumbled landing.For the sit:  Sit in the hole with an incut left sidepull, and a slopey sidepull in a seam.  Probably adds a little quality and an extra grade.
content.protection: I had 1 big pad and two little ones.

content.description: Start as for Monorail (with a jug on the arête) with Liger and Double Edge Sword at your back.  Climb the tall face and continue onwards to the summit via the airy and easy slab.  Really good, probably one of the best of the grade in the park!
content.location: Just left of liger.  Just below the Oval Office cave.  Left of Beautiful and the Bold.

content.description: Start on a good low jug on the right side of the face in the hole.  Trend leftward across the face and once you wrap the corner you have sent.
content.location: Face just left of Liger and Double Edge sword

content.description: Starts on a left crimper and a right slopey dimple and follows the right arete.
content.location: Just up and left of Iron Jesus.

content.description: Start sitting, matched on an edge.  Climb up the beautiful and tall arete.
Start low on a large jug and climb directly up the face using larger sidepulls.
content.location: 50 yards uphill from the Beautiful and the Bold project.

content.description: Start sitting, with a left sidepull seam, and a right undercling.  Climb up the tall face.  The first few moves are the crux, the finish is fairly serious.  Named after an incredible pinch hold that's used.
content.location: Just above and right of Liger.  If you were going to throw a top rope down Liger this problem is right by where you would set up the anchor.

content.description: Start sitting in the corner of the room.  Climb up and leftward, encountering a shoulder intensive crux sequence.  Move left above the beginning of Oval office, wrap around the arete, and follow the airy top out of Oval office.  Really fun and 20 plus moves.
An eliminate to some extent, but really cool movement..   Start sitting on a right facing sidepull (Same start as Toad Princess). Climb straight up, not using the big ledge right.

Offwidth. Start with feet on an obvious mini-ledge just inside the crack. It's your last 'foot' for a while so savor it!About halfway up, a break in the face provides some very good holds to assist in the rest of the kneebar elbow parade. There is a 5-star hand jam towards the top to help prepare for a top out. The top out is tricky and falling would be hard to protect. It is however possible to bail onto the tree if necessary.
content.location: Once you have shimmied up into the small corridor containing The Uninviting, this inviting crack is located to your right. The top is marked by a friendly tree.

content.description:
Climbs the obvious crack in the corner. Start under the roof on two good finger locks. Sink some super fun jams through the low roof into some easier but more committing moves to the top.  

  The top is a bad place to fall, but you can bail onto the opposing slab pretty easily if things get sketchy... 

  Gave it 4 stars because the movement was so fun... Maybe deserves less because of the goofy landing situation...
content.location: About 100 feet or so left of the B&B project. This climb starts in the big pit.

content.description: Start sitting with you left hand on a good down pulling ledge, and right on a low pinch on the face.  Squeeze up the tall pillar.  This is just left of Liger.
Start with a right hand crimp and a good left hand side pull. Make some easier moves straight up the face. The crux is getting over the lip onto the slab. Probably best not to fall at this point.
content.protection: Pads, spotters, and a good head.
content.location: About 100 feet or so left of the B&B project. Its in with a large cluster of highly concentrated problems.

content.description: Get established on big eye feature on slap.  Balance your way up to the right to sloping jug.  Work the arete and top-out.
content.location: This sits in a large pit about 40ft south along the bluff from the Mega Man boulder.

content.description: Start low and left on a jug with a big foot hold and with a right crimp. Pull the roof and throw to a jug.
content.location: On the entrance to the cave where Iron Jesus is.

content.description: Nice little area hidden in the trees above the Slant boulder field.
